etymologies: 1950s: representing an abbreviated form of fracture

definitions: inject liquid into (a subterranean rock formation, borehole, etc.) at high pressure so as to force open existing fissures and extract oil or gas

examples.text: millions of gallons of water are needed to successfully frack a single well
a gas company wants to frack his land and the land around it

shortDefinitions: inject liquid into subterranean rock formation at high pressure to extract oil or gas

definitions: extract (oil or gas) by injecting liquid into a subterranean rock formation, borehole, etc. at high pressure

examples.text: the industry has begun to frack natural gas from shale deposits

shortDefinitions: extract oil or gas by injecting liquid into subterranean rock formation

etymologies: 1970s: euphemistic alteration of fuck, popularized by the US television show Battlestar Galactica

definitions: used to express annoyance, frustration, impatience, or surprise

examples.text: what the frack is going on!

shortDefinitions: used to express annoyance, frustration, etc.
